  <div class="attributed-text-segment-list__container relative mt-1 mb-1.5 babybear:mt-0 babybear:mb-0.5">
    <p class="attributed-text-segment-list__content text-color-text !text-sm whitespace-pre-wrap break-words
         comment__text babybear:mt-0.5" dir="ltr">Congratulations Ford Motor Company!!! 

My grandfather (who is 104 and lives in Dearborn, MI) was hired by Henry Ford himself.  My first car was a Ford and my cousin George Barnes Sr. Owner of  <a class="link" href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/heritage-optical?trk=article-ssr-frontend-pulse_x-social-details_comments-action_comment-text" target="_self" data-tracking-control-name="article-ssr-frontend-pulse_x-social-details_comments-action_comment-text" data-tracking-will-navigate>Heritage Optical</a>  has been purchasing Ford vehicles from ever since I can remember.  So my family has had ties to Ford Motor company for over 80 years.  More importantly during my time in automotive manufacturing the Ford Motor Company consistently showed its commitment to quality (which I feel is industry leading within the American OEM market and several foreign brands) which continue to improve every year.

Ford’s renued commitment to EV (my wife <a class="link" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/teresa-baker-25434148?trk=article-ssr-frontend-pulse_x-social-details_comments-action_comment-text" target="_self" data-tracking-control-name="article-ssr-frontend-pulse_x-social-details_comments-action_comment-text" data-tracking-will-navigate>Teresa Baker</a> loves her new Mach E) and clean energy is reassuring, as they continue to build vehicles for future generations and to partner with corporations like Tesla to provide affordable charging solutions to the masses. 

I am praying for another 120 years of vehicles that are built “Ford tough”!</p>
<!---->  </div>

            
